1
00:01:43,540 --> 00:01:45,410
There's a duel!

2
00:01:46,520 --> 00:01:49,480
Generalissimo will fight
the fabled Prince Sanji!

3
00:01:49,480 --> 00:01:50,710
Prince Sanji?

4
00:01:50,710 --> 00:01:52,540
What kind of guy is he?!

5
00:01:52,540 --> 00:01:54,670
All we know is what he looks like!

6
00:02:01,140 --> 00:02:03,980
I heard he was still refusing to marry,

7
00:02:03,980 --> 00:02:05,930
so I tried to teach him a
lesson on Father's behalf.

8
00:02:05,930 --> 00:02:08,730
Just like the old days.

9
00:02:08,730 --> 00:02:13,980
And this is what happened!
He'll pay for this! Sanji, that bastard!

10
00:02:13,980 --> 00:02:17,610
No, Your Highness, a hammer won't do.

11
00:02:25,610 --> 00:02:28,900
I'm gonna press it. Stay still.

12
00:02:31,880 --> 00:02:33,800
It's fixed.

13
00:02:37,340 --> 00:02:43,180
Damn!
That bastard! He's just a failure...

14
00:02:46,180 --> 00:02:48,830
So that's Prince Sanji!

15
00:02:53,400 --> 00:02:55,570
Are you ready?

16
00:02:57,030 --> 00:02:58,610
Anytime.

17
00:02:58,610 --> 00:02:59,700
All right!

18
00:03:01,280 --> 00:03:02,870
Here I come!

19
00:03:21,430 --> 00:03:22,820
What speed!

20
00:03:22,820 --> 00:03:26,760
That's just what you'd expect
from a wanted pirate!

21
00:03:41,360 --> 00:03:43,900
How dare you kick your real father!

22
00:03:44,120 --> 00:03:46,700
Cut it out! You started this!

23
00:03:46,700 --> 00:03:50,830
And you'd better stop saying
that you're my father!

24
00:03:52,830 --> 00:03:56,700
You're my son who came back! Sanji!

25
00:03:56,700 --> 00:03:59,420
Don't say that while you're attacking me!

26
00:03:59,490 --> 00:04:00,820
He's strong!

27
00:04:00,820 --> 00:04:03,400
He doesn't even have a raid suit on!

28
00:04:04,430 --> 00:04:08,760
I'll go back to my pirate ship
as soon as the tea party ends.

29
00:04:08,760 --> 00:04:10,640
I'll just pretend to marry her!

30
00:04:10,640 --> 00:04:12,230
You're still saying that?!

31
00:04:14,900 --> 00:04:19,730
You just want the bond between
you guys and Big Mom, don't you?

32
00:04:19,730 --> 00:04:22,450
Then it doesn't matter where I end up!

33
00:04:22,860 --> 00:04:24,520
You can't do that!

34
00:04:24,520 --> 00:04:27,120
It would be seen as the
Vinsmoke family's betrayal!

35
00:04:27,120 --> 00:04:29,790
You think Big Mom would allow that?!

36
00:04:29,790 --> 00:04:34,200
I don't care what happens to you guys afterward.

37
00:04:34,200 --> 00:04:38,210
I just came here to protect my friends!

38
00:04:38,210 --> 00:04:40,550
You would forsake your own family?!

39
00:04:41,800 --> 00:04:45,260
You guys are not my family!

40
00:04:48,470 --> 00:04:50,920
He was in the kitchen, as I thought.

41
00:04:50,920 --> 00:04:54,780
He was making food for rats again!

42
00:04:56,850 --> 00:04:59,700
Royalty mustn't cook.

43
00:05:00,440 --> 00:05:03,440
Shut up! Give it back!

44
00:05:04,490 --> 00:05:06,740
Ouch...

45
00:05:09,410 --> 00:05:11,060
You idiot!

46
00:05:11,060 --> 00:05:13,250
Don't touch me!

47
00:05:15,240 --> 00:05:17,630
He's so weak and pathetic!

48
00:05:17,630 --> 00:05:19,540
We were all born on the same day!

49
00:05:19,880 --> 00:05:22,500
Why are you such a failure, while we're not?!

50
00:05:33,770 --> 00:05:35,560
You failure!

51
00:05:48,150 --> 00:05:50,530
Oh, Father!

52
00:05:52,080 --> 00:05:54,240
Are you beating up Sanji again?

53
00:05:57,480 --> 00:05:59,380
Help me!

54
00:06:00,460 --> 00:06:02,210
Father!

55
00:06:03,760 --> 00:06:05,360
Why?

56
00:06:06,880 --> 00:06:10,090
"Why?"

57
00:06:10,090 --> 00:06:15,100
I don't think you're gonna be a good soldier in the future.

58
00:06:15,100 --> 00:06:19,350
I have no obligation to help you,
and you're not worth raising.

59
00:06:25,320 --> 00:06:27,270
Father!

60
00:06:27,270 --> 00:06:30,660
You're a disgrace to our family!

61
00:06:40,080 --> 00:06:43,130
Stand up! I'll train you!

62
00:06:45,090 --> 00:06:47,880
A disgrace to the Vinsmokes!

63
00:06:47,880 --> 00:06:50,350
Go ahead and make a charge at him, Yonji.

64
00:06:50,350 --> 00:06:52,090
Okay!

65
00:07:20,580 --> 00:07:23,600
Did you remember something?!

66
00:07:25,170 --> 00:07:27,050
He blocked the blade with his leg!

67
00:07:31,590 --> 00:07:34,600
To think the Sanji I knew can now use haki...

68
00:07:35,220 --> 00:07:36,720
Give me a sword!

69
00:07:36,720 --> 00:07:38,310
Y-Yes, sir!

70
00:07:42,320 --> 00:07:43,440
Take it.

71
00:07:45,180 --> 00:07:46,600
What's wrong?

72
00:07:46,600 --> 00:07:49,400
I thought I taught you how to use a sword.

73
00:07:54,450 --> 00:07:59,660
I'm not gonna use my hands for such crap.

74
00:08:08,700 --> 00:08:10,630
My hands...

75
00:08:10,630 --> 00:08:13,550
are for cooking only.

76
00:08:45,790 --> 00:08:49,710
Oh, that weak little Sanji
became this strong...

77
00:08:49,710 --> 00:08:52,840
Cooking? That's absurd!

78
00:08:52,840 --> 00:08:58,100
Do you still cook for rats?
Royalty mustn't offer services!

79
00:08:58,100 --> 00:08:59,690
How embarrassing!

80
00:09:00,420 --> 00:09:02,180
That's ridiculous.

81
00:09:09,150 --> 00:09:13,900
What problem do you have with this marriage?!

82
00:09:23,160 --> 00:09:25,020
Generalissimo's hand-to-hand combat!

83
00:09:25,020 --> 00:09:27,750
The fighting style of the man
known as "Garuda"!

84
00:09:27,750 --> 00:09:29,840
It's a rare sight to behold!

85
00:09:29,840 --> 00:09:33,880
An aerial attack?
Ironically, this is my forte.

86
00:09:34,740 --> 00:09:36,950
Diable Jambe!

87
00:09:36,950 --> 00:09:38,280
Collier...

88
00:09:41,250 --> 00:09:43,160
Shoot!

89
00:09:55,070 --> 00:09:58,410
War advances science!

90
00:10:00,340 --> 00:10:02,640
Electromagnetic Crack!

91
00:10:04,570 --> 00:10:07,020
Blaster!

92
00:10:25,720 --> 00:10:30,840
The Germa that you once knew
is a thing of the past now!

93
00:10:56,080 --> 00:10:57,420
So, hey...

94
00:10:58,040 --> 00:11:00,050
Can I ask you something?

95
00:11:03,890 --> 00:11:08,480
Do you think being a biological parent
entitles someone to respect?

96
00:11:09,810 --> 00:11:11,650
You don't...

97
00:11:15,040 --> 00:11:19,860
have a single good
memory of him... do you?

98
00:11:26,800 --> 00:11:27,990
You...

99
00:11:28,320 --> 00:11:31,580
Father! Let me out!

100
00:11:32,880 --> 00:11:34,660
...suffered so much.

101
00:11:43,340 --> 00:11:47,560
Father! It's too dark!

102
00:11:50,550 --> 00:11:54,000
Poêle à Frire...

103
00:11:54,540 --> 00:11:58,230
You only have animosity toward him.

104
00:12:01,850 --> 00:12:02,880
Wall!

105
00:12:07,830 --> 00:12:10,080
Hey, you guys, move!

106
00:12:34,590 --> 00:12:35,820
Electromagnetic...

107
00:12:35,820 --> 00:12:37,130
Shaft!

108
00:13:01,610 --> 00:13:04,260
You're tough as nails. I'm surprised.

109
00:13:08,350 --> 00:13:13,020
I can't believe you're
that weak little Sanji.

110
00:13:13,020 --> 00:13:14,820
This is getting ridiculous.

111
00:13:14,820 --> 00:13:17,600
I wanna attend the tea party
and get out of here already.

112
00:13:17,600 --> 00:13:21,030
Then I'm gonna be free from
the curse of Big Mom's invitation.

113
00:13:21,530 --> 00:13:26,200
I thought you might've changed a little,
but you've actually gotten worse!

114
00:13:26,200 --> 00:13:29,990
Get out of this room, old man!
You're a stranger to me!

115
00:13:29,990 --> 00:13:35,410
No, you have my blood in your veins.

116
00:13:35,410 --> 00:13:39,080
Don't get me wrong.
All Germa soldiers are...

117
00:13:39,080 --> 00:13:46,800
followers who are willing to die 
for the Vinsmoke family at a moment's notice!

118
00:13:46,800 --> 00:13:50,970
They're Germa's biggest military force!

119
00:13:53,360 --> 00:13:58,350
Then, why don't you use them 
to make your stupid dream come true?

120
00:13:58,350 --> 00:14:04,100
Conquering the North Blue? Great!
That's perfect for an evil organization.

121
00:14:04,100 --> 00:14:07,650
You're quick on the uptake.
That's right.

122
00:14:07,650 --> 00:14:09,860
By joining hands with Big Mom,

123
00:14:09,860 --> 00:14:12,620
it'll become an objective
I can achieve for sure!

124
00:14:12,620 --> 00:14:15,870
An objective... I can achieve for sure!

125
00:14:18,460 --> 00:14:23,000
If you can understand that,
I have nothing left to say.

126
00:14:23,890 --> 00:14:28,430
I wanted to somehow settle this 
with you peacefully, but...

127
00:14:32,100 --> 00:14:37,600
I need Big Mom's help,
but the condition is establishing blood ties.

128
00:14:37,600 --> 00:14:39,780
It's just a marriage,

129
00:14:39,780 --> 00:14:45,110
but I can't let any of my precious sons
marry someone from that crazy old bag's family!

130
00:14:46,610 --> 00:14:51,880
Then I remembered... I have another son...

131
00:14:51,880 --> 00:14:54,220
who was a failure.

132
00:14:55,450 --> 00:14:59,230
You are a sacrifice, Sanji.

133
00:14:59,230 --> 00:15:02,020
I haven't changed.

134
00:15:02,020 --> 00:15:06,920
I don't think of you as my son even one bit!

135
00:15:11,310 --> 00:15:13,470
Hey, what are these?

136
00:15:13,470 --> 00:15:16,160
You said your hands are important to you.

137
00:15:16,160 --> 00:15:17,770
That's great.

138
00:15:18,390 --> 00:15:23,010
Do you know the shackle collars
that the Celestial Dragons' slaves wear?

139
00:15:23,610 --> 00:15:28,320
If they try to escape from their masters,
they'll explode along with their heads.

140
00:15:28,800 --> 00:15:30,880
Those work the same way.

141
00:15:30,880 --> 00:15:34,950
If you try to escape this island,
your hands will be blown off!

142
00:15:35,450 --> 00:15:37,790
Screw you! Take them off!

143
00:15:37,790 --> 00:15:41,460
Big Mom had the foresight to lend them to me.

144
00:15:41,460 --> 00:15:44,130
She has the key.

145
00:15:44,130 --> 00:15:45,790
What?!

146
00:15:49,340 --> 00:15:51,000
Don't do that.

147
00:15:54,650 --> 00:15:57,930
You can't try to rip them off.

148
00:15:57,930 --> 00:16:02,850
Using the key is the only way
to take them off, of course.

149
00:16:05,320 --> 00:16:08,070
You can't escape.

150
00:16:08,070 --> 00:16:10,360
Well, first of all,

151
00:16:10,910 --> 00:16:15,120
we Germa won't let you get away!

152
00:16:18,080 --> 00:16:20,910
You have to get married!

153
00:16:25,890 --> 00:16:29,340
Extra! Extra!

154
00:16:29,340 --> 00:16:32,050
Boss Jinbe betrayed us?!

155
00:16:32,050 --> 00:16:35,050
This happened between him and Mama yesterday?

156
00:16:36,310 --> 00:16:42,310
Boss Jinbe was so cool
when he stopped Mama's tantrum.

157
00:16:42,310 --> 00:16:45,560
He blustered that he
wanted to leave her crew,

158
00:16:45,560 --> 00:16:49,280
but he got scared of paying
the price and backed down!

159
00:16:49,280 --> 00:16:52,200
Yeah? That's pathetic!

160
00:16:53,080 --> 00:16:54,780
What a loser!

161
00:16:54,780 --> 00:16:58,740
I guess "Knight of the Sea" is only a title.
I've lost respect for him.

162
00:16:58,740 --> 00:17:02,040
So he was a coward and a traitor.

163
00:17:05,920 --> 00:17:07,460
Jinbe-san...

164
00:17:07,460 --> 00:17:10,840
I didn't know you were working under Big Mom.

165
00:17:10,840 --> 00:17:14,630
That's why Fishman Island
was protected by Big Mom.

166
00:17:16,240 --> 00:17:20,720
Jinbe is a former warlord, isn't he?

167
00:17:20,720 --> 00:17:23,180
I can't believe someone of his stature is her subordinate.

168
00:17:23,180 --> 00:17:26,280
Brook, do you know this man?

169
00:17:26,280 --> 00:17:30,850
Yes, he's a very important person to us.

170
00:17:30,850 --> 00:17:36,400
I must still complete that journey. 
Once I am able to move freely again,

171
00:17:36,400 --> 00:17:42,080
I promise I will join your crew.

172
00:17:42,160 --> 00:17:46,650
I guess he turned down 
the offer to join our crew that day,

173
00:17:46,650 --> 00:17:50,540
because he wanted to fulfill
his duty to Big Mom.

174
00:17:51,590 --> 00:17:56,360
Now, this article...
It doesn't sound like something he'd do.

175
00:17:56,360 --> 00:17:59,280
He won't come and join us anymore?

176
00:17:59,280 --> 00:18:01,590
Hey, Brook!

177
00:18:03,990 --> 00:18:06,950
Please! I have to go somewhere!

178
00:18:06,950 --> 00:18:11,240
Nothing is more important to you now
than choosing a dress!

179
00:18:11,240 --> 00:18:14,480
Stop being such a baby-s'il vous plaît,
Madam Pudding!

180
00:18:14,480 --> 00:18:15,710
But...

181
00:18:15,710 --> 00:18:17,740
Madam Pudding!

182
00:18:17,740 --> 00:18:19,700
How about this dress?

183
00:18:19,700 --> 00:18:21,330
Wow, it looks good on you!

184
00:18:21,330 --> 00:18:26,290
How about this one? I knew it, Madam Pudding!
It looks wonderful!

185
00:18:26,290 --> 00:18:29,500
Everything looks good on you!

186
00:18:29,500 --> 00:18:32,060
Which one do you like, Madam Pudding?

187
00:18:32,060 --> 00:18:33,350
Um...

188
00:18:33,350 --> 00:18:36,710
Madam Pudding,
do you know what the groom likes?

189
00:18:36,710 --> 00:18:40,610
What?!
No! I've only met him once, so...

190
00:18:40,610 --> 00:18:42,300
Whaaat?!

191
00:18:42,300 --> 00:18:46,110
Wait a minute, Pudding-san,
what is she doing here?!

192
00:18:46,110 --> 00:18:49,560
I guess she got caught by her attendants.

193
00:18:49,560 --> 00:18:52,540
I assumed she'd already led Sanji-san out

194
00:18:52,540 --> 00:18:55,700
to meet with Luffy-san and the others by now.

195
00:18:55,700 --> 00:19:00,290
Looking at this, I bet Sanji 
doesn't even know that we're here.

196
00:19:00,290 --> 00:19:03,950
Then, who did Luffy-san see at the shore?

197
00:19:03,950 --> 00:19:08,790
I don't know.
Maybe he just saw someone else.

198
00:19:11,460 --> 00:19:16,890
That's... If I'm not mistaken,
he was on Big Mom's ship...

199
00:19:16,890 --> 00:19:19,170
Yeah, I know him very well.

200
00:19:19,170 --> 00:19:21,430
Baron Tamago!

201
00:19:24,830 --> 00:19:28,450
Baron Tamago, may I speak to you?

202
00:19:33,960 --> 00:19:36,270
What is it-soir ?

203
00:19:36,270 --> 00:19:40,240
The Straw Hats' ship that stopped by
at Chocolat Town yesterday...

204
00:19:40,320 --> 00:19:43,160
They already know!

205
00:19:43,160 --> 00:19:50,330
When they left, Mr. Pekoms, who was guiding them,
was already gone, they say.

206
00:19:50,330 --> 00:19:52,620
They know everything!

207
00:19:52,620 --> 00:19:57,890
As for the four Straw Hats
who wandered into the Seducing Woods today...

208
00:19:56,260 --> 00:20:01,720
Carrot's Poster: "Bunny Mink."

209
00:19:57,890 --> 00:20:01,720
they're already cornered!
As good as captured!

210
00:20:01,720 --> 00:20:05,510
Luffy-san and the others got caught?!

211
00:20:05,510 --> 00:20:08,770
But we still can't find the remaining two.

212
00:20:08,770 --> 00:20:10,930
Pedro's Poster: "Leopard Mink."

213
00:20:08,770 --> 00:20:10,930
These two.

214
00:20:10,980 --> 00:20:13,940
That's us!

215
00:20:13,940 --> 00:20:17,520
It's leaked out completely!
They knew everything from the start!

216
00:20:17,520 --> 00:20:20,280
Where were they watching us from?!

217
00:20:20,280 --> 00:20:24,890
That mink is not a leopard-soir.

218
00:20:20,280 --> 00:20:24,890
Pedro's Poster: "Leopard Mink."

219
00:20:24,870 --> 00:20:28,530
He's a jaguar mink. His name is Pedro.

220
00:20:29,080 --> 00:20:30,500
Do you know him?

221
00:20:31,060 --> 00:20:34,290
Just a little bit from the past.

222
00:20:37,650 --> 00:20:43,840
I know what he would do-feuille.

223
00:20:43,840 --> 00:20:48,390
– Anyway, I want you guys to look for Pekoms.
– Yes, sir.

224
00:20:50,830 --> 00:20:55,660
Pekoms. Since he was alive-bon,

225
00:20:55,660 --> 00:20:58,140
for the sake of our
long-standing partnership,

226
00:20:58,140 --> 00:21:02,650
I was going to ask
Mama to pardon him.

227
00:21:04,760 --> 00:21:07,950
He gives me a lot of trouble-marron.

228
00:21:07,950 --> 00:21:12,790
We are in big trouble!

229
00:21:15,600 --> 00:21:18,460
Hey, cut it out, junior!

230
00:21:18,460 --> 00:21:20,840
Quiet!

231
00:21:26,340 --> 00:21:30,220
Oh, he's laughing! That's good!

232
00:21:33,100 --> 00:21:38,100
Good, good, good, good! You're a good boy!

233
00:21:38,100 --> 00:21:43,990
Hey, junior.
I hope you'll become a great boss like me one day.

234
00:21:46,360 --> 00:21:49,120
I can't stand watching that!

235
00:21:49,970 --> 00:21:52,510
He's dazzling, isn't he?

236
00:21:52,510 --> 00:21:55,540
He was just born.

237
00:21:55,540 --> 00:21:58,620
And you're going to die.

238
00:22:00,100 --> 00:22:05,630
Don't you think it's an exquisite contrast?
It's like a painting.

239
00:22:07,010 --> 00:22:10,650
This is what you chose.

240
00:22:10,650 --> 00:22:13,850
Pekoms. I gave you a chance.

241
00:22:13,850 --> 00:22:17,850
It didn't look like a chance to me.

242
00:22:17,850 --> 00:22:20,560
Remember what happened to you on Zou.

243
00:22:20,560 --> 00:22:24,190
Human empathy isn't worth anything.

244
00:22:25,990 --> 00:22:30,780
You're not cut out for this business.

245
00:22:31,450 --> 00:22:36,830
This is the perfect place
for getting rid of someone.

246
00:22:43,460 --> 00:22:45,550
Any last words?

247
00:23:11,240 --> 00:23:14,620
You underestimate Mama too much!

248
00:23:51,110 --> 00:23:53,870
Now, let me see your hands.

249
00:23:55,530 --> 00:23:57,540
They're covered in bruises.

250
00:24:06,370 --> 00:24:08,250
Little eggplant!

251
00:24:08,800 --> 00:24:10,590
Ouch!

252
00:24:16,060 --> 00:24:17,970
What's your problem, you damn geezer?!

253
00:24:17,970 --> 00:24:22,190
Are your hands for fighting?!

254
00:24:35,190 --> 00:24:37,560
Dammit!

255
00:24:52,590 --> 00:24:58,890
I think I invested enough money,
Caesar Clown.

256
00:24:58,890 --> 00:25:04,100
Y-Y-Y-Y-Yes!
And of course, I didn't stop researching!

257
00:25:04,700 --> 00:25:07,210
My dream is...

258
00:25:22,370 --> 00:25:27,000
for all races in the
world to become family

259
00:25:27,000 --> 00:25:31,570
and sit around a dining table
at the same eye level.

260
00:25:31,570 --> 00:25:34,670
They'll drink what I drink,

261
00:25:36,260 --> 00:25:39,970
and eat what I eat!

262
00:25:47,810 --> 00:25:50,820
Isn't that a wonderful dream?!

263
00:25:50,820 --> 00:25:55,280
And you're gonna make it come true for me,
Caesar!

264
00:25:57,160 --> 00:26:03,500
I want you to make my family members gigantic
with the power of science.

265
00:26:03,500 --> 00:26:06,890
You kept telling me

266
00:26:06,890 --> 00:26:13,500
that you were almost done,
but needed a little more research money.

267
00:26:13,500 --> 00:26:17,320
I was excited and
spent quite a lot of money.

268
00:26:17,320 --> 00:26:20,090
So how're the results?

269
00:26:20,090 --> 00:26:24,180
Well, thanks to you, they're quite good!

270
00:26:24,960 --> 00:26:29,410
The gigantification of the human body.
Yes, I was doing experiments.

271
00:26:29,410 --> 00:26:33,460
The whole world is
looking for a technology like that.

272
00:26:33,460 --> 00:26:39,340
But I was performing experiments
to turn kids into giants. It was deadly.

273
00:26:39,340 --> 00:26:43,720
It's impossible to make a drug
that'll magically

274
00:26:43,720 --> 00:26:47,080
make people gigantic
like this old bag wants.

275
00:26:47,080 --> 00:26:51,380
That's why I just screwed her
out of her money, and...

276
00:26:55,050 --> 00:26:58,100
called girls' ships over
to the island every night,

277
00:26:58,100 --> 00:27:02,990
and spent all the money
on alcohol and women!

278
00:27:05,990 --> 00:27:11,860
Those were the good old days!
I was going nuts behind Joker's back!

279
00:27:11,860 --> 00:27:13,060
"Doflamingo Falls!"

280
00:27:13,150 --> 00:27:16,480
I didn't expect Joker to be defeated...

281
00:27:23,070 --> 00:27:27,200
and my life to become this miserable!

282
00:27:27,200 --> 00:27:32,330
Dammit! It was much easier back then!

283
00:27:32,330 --> 00:27:35,250
This is all because of that...

284
00:27:35,250 --> 00:27:37,260
Are you giving a facial performance?

285
00:27:38,910 --> 00:27:40,340
No!

286
00:27:40,340 --> 00:27:46,060
This! And that! And everything!
This is all Straw Hat Luffy's fault!

287
00:27:46,060 --> 00:27:50,980
Big Mom! I was doing the research
without sleeping at all!

288
00:27:50,980 --> 00:27:54,440
And when it was almost complete,

289
00:27:54,440 --> 00:27:58,690
Straw Hat and Trafalgar Law showed up!

290
00:28:05,620 --> 00:28:10,540
If it weren't for them,
the gigantism drug would've been complete!

291
00:28:10,540 --> 00:28:13,420
Because I'm a genius!

292
00:28:14,460 --> 00:28:17,580
It's a shame that the lab
built by the World Government,

293
00:28:17,580 --> 00:28:20,170
and all its high-level technology,
was destroyed!

294
00:28:20,170 --> 00:28:24,720
I could only achieve the results
in that perfectly controlled environment!

295
00:28:26,530 --> 00:28:31,730
The vast amount of money you invested
and that lab!

296
00:28:31,730 --> 00:28:38,440
I lost them, so I can't create
the gigantism drug now!

297
00:28:38,440 --> 00:28:41,280
I can't!

298
00:28:53,020 --> 00:28:57,790
I built the exact same lab
as the one on Punk Hazard.

299
00:28:57,790 --> 00:28:58,840
What?!

300
00:28:58,840 --> 00:29:02,090
I got the blueprints to it ages ago.

301
00:29:02,090 --> 00:29:08,220
Our minister of candy's 
amezaiku skills are quite versatile.

302
00:29:02,090 --> 00:29:08,220
"Amezaiku" – Japanese candy craft artistry

303
00:29:08,220 --> 00:29:12,190
You can spend as much money as you want
for the research.

304
00:29:12,190 --> 00:29:13,770
What?!

305
00:29:13,770 --> 00:29:16,940
A-A-A-A... A-Are you sure?!

306
00:29:16,940 --> 00:29:20,280
I mean, I appreciate it!

307
00:29:20,280 --> 00:29:21,150
So?

308
00:29:21,760 --> 00:29:22,820
"So?"

309
00:29:24,450 --> 00:29:26,360
When will it be ready?

310
00:29:29,280 --> 00:29:33,250
In a week? Or two weeks?

311
00:29:37,630 --> 00:29:40,960
I can't wait!

312
00:29:41,750 --> 00:29:47,140
Don't be ridiculous!
Mankind has been doing this research for centuries,

313
00:29:47,140 --> 00:29:50,180
but no one's ever succeeded!

314
00:29:55,350 --> 00:29:58,020
Lick! Lick!

315
00:29:58,020 --> 00:30:01,520
Do you like it, Caesar-kun ?

316
00:30:04,030 --> 00:30:07,200
It seems to be quite authentic, doesn't it?

317
00:30:08,360 --> 00:30:12,620
The inside is exactly like the way it was, too. Lick!

318
00:30:17,290 --> 00:30:19,000
That's...

319
00:30:19,000 --> 00:30:21,250
No! Don't do that!

320
00:30:23,590 --> 00:30:25,840
This is fun.

321
00:30:31,180 --> 00:30:33,520
Dammit!

322
00:30:35,700 --> 00:30:38,900
We've arrived at Whole Cake Island.

323
00:30:41,610 --> 00:30:44,360
Wait! Hey, Black Leg!

324
00:30:44,360 --> 00:30:47,740
Give me back my heart before you go!

325
00:30:47,740 --> 00:30:49,610
Oh.

326
00:30:49,610 --> 00:30:50,700
Okay.

327
00:30:56,500 --> 00:31:01,420
You only have two weeks to
produce the gigantism drug!

328
00:31:01,420 --> 00:31:07,550
If it takes longer than that,
I'll turn you into a candy man and lick you!

329
00:31:09,470 --> 00:31:11,500
I'll be killed in two weeks!

330
00:31:11,500 --> 00:31:14,220
I gotta do something!

331
00:31:20,730 --> 00:31:24,690
I've seen you dozens of times now.

332
00:31:27,360 --> 00:31:29,000
It's you again.

333
00:31:29,000 --> 00:31:30,530
I found another one.

334
00:31:33,700 --> 00:31:36,900
There are so many of them!

335
00:31:52,130 --> 00:31:54,700
Anyway...

336
00:32:11,570 --> 00:32:14,620
How did you guys multiply?!

